Experiment_Feedback: The sliders used to rate attractiveness, beauty and symmetry made it difficult/confusing to accurately express my answers at times
I found it a bit hard to rate attractiveness and beauty of the people shown since I felt bad for them if I found them ugly/unattractive

With the identification of faces as being either AI or real, there's no way to capture the response of "this could easily be either!". I feel that AI has got to a point of being able to generate very real faces - so much so that unless you scrutinise an image and find a seemingly obvious 'error', it's virtually impossible to tell. Therefore my responses followed a pattern where the more unusual a face appeared to be, the more I would tend to select AI generated, because there is no option to leave the slider right in the middle for 'totally unsure'. But I'm not sure that is really the point of the experiment!
